It is essentially the original version with baked LBW 1,1,1,1,1,1,1,1,0.2,0.7,1,1,1,1,1,1,1 You can skip download if you have no problem using LoRA block weight extension, but some people reported that it could not work together with highres fix so I made this stand-alone version.

Please consider put blurry background, blurry foreground, blurry in negative prompts, switch to another highres fix model like UltraSharp or use lower highres fix denoising strength when you fall into such cases.

Ishtar (Swimsuit Rider) LoRA

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

This model was trained using 43 images of Ishtar's Swimsuit Rider version. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime based models.

Recommended weight is between 0.8 and 1.

Trigger word is Ishtar.

Example images were generated using JafaMix v4 with 30 steps, then hires. fixed with 20 steps by 1.5

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: Viera - Final Fantasy Tactics Advance
items.description:
I am the Reindeer Czar and I love deer and wolves! Even though this is true, I love the Viera from Final Fantasy Tactics Advance. Fighting alongside them gave me many great memories. Add them to your SD art, and have adventures. I saw a model for Viera like Fran, but not the style from FFTA. So I made this one. It turned out pretty decent. It is not perfect, but was trained from the original artwork.

I prompt in three parts:

First part - The basic attributes.

(viera, dark skin, brown eyes, long hair) or short hair if you like.

Second Part - Her clothes and what she's doing.

(dress, slit dress) if you like.

Third Part - Her setting.

(outdoor, forest)

Weigh the lora from 0.75 to 1 for best results. Though 1.0 is very good. Some models are better than others. I put the best ones from testing in the post. Lawlassyiffymix20_Furry works best I think.

NeatnessFluffyFur model adds a tail to her, so probably don't use that one.

Enjoy! Share pictures if you like!

items.name: Watanabe Saki (Shinsekai Yori)
items.description:
This is a lycors\locon you have to use the additional networks extension or the lycoris extension for this to work.

If you want to stay updated check out my Twitter

So time for another one. So I was really confused when i watched the anime the first time and the community is pretty split on if it is a masterpiece or a disaster. From memory I would say I liked it but I would have to rewatch it to give a recommendation.

I didn't train on pictures of the anime I chose to stick to the manga because I like her design more for obvious reasons.

In the manga she skips the child phase and goes straight from this to full adult. Which I prefer because I really hate how children are depicted in anime they don't really behave like real children they are more like small adults.

I used "Shinsekai" as activation token because "Saki" and and "Watanabe Saki" or just "Watanabe" where all already associated with a character. Saki might have worked but all the other combination were doomed because this model has one or two problems that make it a bit weird to use.

The problems are that there are only 3 colored images in the dataset. You don't get monochrom pictures though unless you tag for them. The real problem is that the model doesn't know the right colors for her hair and her eyes (funny enough it gets the clothes right most of the time).

I used brown hair and purple eyes for the preview pictures but you can also use purple hair or black hair and you can also change the eyecolor with ease I think. You can also change her outfit and if you go to strength 0.8 or below it shouldn't have any resemblance to her default outfit. Only this outfit is included i tried to get the outfit from the first chapters as well but it doesn't really work.

Thanks for reading and if you like the model you can leave a like, rate and comment that would be appreciated.

Have fun generating.

items.name: gaybleached | light topping dark yaoi
items.description:
When prompting for sex acts and including a 'dark skin' tag, most models will have the dark skinned character topping. Using this LoHa will generally reverse that, in the case of male/male sex specifically.

Pinups are easy, sex is difficult. Many models can't do it well or at all. I recommend AllBoyMix and other mixes from Bodlo for good yaoi sex poses. Using sex position Loras could also help.

There is no trigger word, just use "dark skin", "light skin", or "dark-skinned male", "light-skinned male", and prompt as usual.

It also has some dark-skinned femboys in the training data, you can prompt "dark-skinned femboy" to make the dark-skinned character smaller and girlier (but still clearly male).

Some example images show a comparison with "bleached", that is an older Lora (doesn't seem to be on civitai?) that basically has this function for hetero scenes. It doesn't really work for yaoi as it tries to make both males lighter, or the darker male into a woman. But it is there because I thought people would be curious how it compared.

"bwc-06" is the original name of the epoch that was chosen for the final version.

items.description:
THERE IS A LORA VERSION OF THIS MODEL AVAILABLE. IT IS EXACTLY THE SAME MODEL AS THIS ONE, EXCEPT IN A DIFFERENT AND LIGHTER FORMAT.

Shivam Dreambooth of American actress Jennifer Connelly, using 125 ref images and 1400 (real) reg images, for 8,000 steps.

The period covered is around 1997-2007. To get a generation of the younger version, put the word young in front of the key prompt, and use brackets to control the degree of youth.

I generally use these models in complex workflows, inpainting faces after initial T2Is, and using ControlNet extensively. So if you're hoping for one-click prompt magic, my models aren't data-curated with this in mind, but rather as tools for traditional workflows that use Photoshop and other older methods.

This model may well produce subject-accurate NSFW output unless countered in negative prompts.

Support needed ! Out of colab credits. You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

You can also subscribe to my Patreon and get exclusive models .

ZZ Top Eliminator is a 1982 hot rod based on a 1933 Ford Model B V8. It belongs to Billy Gibbons (the lead guitarist of the famous blues rock band ZZ Top, founded in 1971 in Houston, Texas). Inspired by the American Kustom Kulture of the 1950s, it has participated in the band's success and international legend as its emblem.

Steps: 50, Sampler: DDIM, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Use Zztop as trigger.

items.name: dragonian, animelike race from rimworld
items.description:
100% game textures in dataset.

we have edited the textures for better result.

v1 Highly recommended:

dragonian, dragonian_body, dragonian_tail,dragonian_hairstyle in prompt and

simple background, black background, chibi, bald in negative prompt

v2 Highly recommended:

dragonian_head, dragonian_horns, dragonian_body, dragonian_tail,dragonian_hairstyle in prompt and

simple background, black background, white background, chibi, bald in negative prompt

Negative prompt above is highly recommended because of the feature of the dataset.

According to my experience, dragon, animal, extra tail also should be add to negative prompt.

The fact is, prompts depends largely on your base model.

After I run all the posts, I changed the Lora file name for easy understanding. Better pay attention when copy the generation data.

items.name: DEMI (APEX-17 D19M45 | Subverse) LoRA
items.description:
The robot DEMI from the game Subverse by Studio FOW. Works best on 0.8-1.0. Training done on NAI.

Trigger: "demisub, colored skin" always needed "makeup, earrings" for face accuracy.

Suggestions:

  • Eyes: "Blue eyes, Red eyes, Pink eyes" for whichever version is to your fancy.

  • "white skin, black hair" can help if you lower weight and things don't stick.

  • "detached collar, ascot, blue leotard, wrist cuffs, white footwear, high heels" for her main outfit.

Sometimes her skin will become paler due to negative embedding so beware you might have to remove it to fix. She is flexible when to comes to controlling the clothes but you need to reduce the weight. This will break body/skin a bit due to unique design and it may be tricky to change color but still possible with some tag experimentation. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.
